  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: GSWGA_Course_1_Lesson_1_Q1
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: "Margaret, a marketing analyst, requests that the company\u2019s AI system
    outline a presentation deck summarizing the first quarter\u2019s results for
    a team meeting.\r\nWhat step of the generative AI process is this?"
  answers:
  - AI analyzes this data, looking for patterns and relationships between the different
    pieces of information.
  - AI is fed a large amount of data. This could be anything from images and sounds
    to text and numbers.
  - AI uses what it has learned to create something new. The neural network generates
    new outputs by inputting a random seed value.
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 02000000
  correctMessage: In this step of the generative AI process, AI uses what it has
    learned to make new content, starting with a random seed value to guide the output.
  incorrectMessage: Not quite. Consider that the AI model has been trained.
